
[1]vesicate

   VES'ICATE, v.t. [L. vesica, a little bladder. Gr. from to inflate.]

   To blister; to raise little bladders, or separate the cuticle by
   inflaming the skin. Celsus recommends to vesicate the external parts of
   wounds.
